query: Jeremiah is riding in a car that is traveling 60 miles per hour. At this rate, how many minutes will it take him to travel 20 miles?
ground_truth: Distance equals rate times time, so the trip will take $$\frac{20\text{ mi.}}{60\text{ mph}}=\frac{1}{3}\text{ hours}.$$  One-third of an hour is $\boxed{20}$ minutes.
answers_list:
[reasoning process] To find out how long it will take Jeremiah to travel 20 miles at a speed of 60 miles per hour, we can start by calculating the time in hours needed to cover that distance. The formula to calculate time is:

\[
\text{Time} = \frac{\text{Distance}}{\text{Speed}}
\]

Substituting in our values:

\[
\text{Time} = \frac{20 \text{ miles}}{60 \text{ miles per hour}} = \frac{1}{3} \text{ hours}
\]

Now, since we need the answer in minutes, we convert hours to minutes. Since 1 hour is equal to 60 minutes, we multiply:

\[
\frac{1}{3} \text{ hours} \times 60 \text{ minutes/hour} = 20 \text{ minutes}
\]

[Verification] We can verify this by checking if traveling 20 miles at 60 miles per hour indeed takes 20 minutes. If we take the speed of 60 miles per hour, in one hour (60 minutes), he would travel 60 miles. Thus, in 20 minutes (which is one-third of an hour), he would travel:

\[
60 \text{ miles/hour} \times \frac{1}{3} \text{ hour} = 20 \text{ miles}
\]

This confirms our calculation.

[Final Answer] The answer is 20 \n#### 20
